    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="How to Scan for SDUs in SAGE?" class="article-title">
          How to Scan for SDUs in SAGE?
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2025-12-08T18:23:53Z" title="2025-12-08T18:23:53Z" data-datetime="relative">December 08, 2025 18:23</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/47053520025747-How-to-Scan-for-SDUs-in-SAGE/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>Survey Data Units (SDUs) are special resources used for crafting and upgrading starbases in Starbased. Scanning is how you find them and it can be a highly rewarding activity if done right.</p><h3 id="h_01KBJ76J01SR89B6GH51WJVC1A">Prepare Your Fleet</h3><p>Before you can scan, make sure your fleet:</p><ul><li><p>Is <strong>undocked</strong> from a Starbase</p></li><li><p>Has enough <strong>Fuel</strong> to move to a sector</p></li><li><p>Has enough <strong>Food</strong> to support scanning (unless using a Data Runner ship)</p></li><li><p>Is equipped with ships that have strong <strong>SDU/Scan</strong> stats</p></li></ul><p><strong>Tip:</strong> The further you are from the Central Space Station (CSS) and the closer to the center of the map, the better your scan odds.</p><h3 id="h_01KBJ76J018QM61MS8XE7MNH15">Understanding SDU Scanning Mechanics</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Scan Cooldown:</strong> The cooldown is determined by the slowest ship in your fleet</p></li><li><p><strong>SDU/Scan Stat:</strong> Each ship contributes to the total number of SDUs your fleet can retrieve per scan</p></li><li><p><strong>Information Density:</strong> This hidden sector stat determines scan success rate and how many SDUs are available</p></li></ul><p><strong>Example:</strong> If your fleet can scan up to 100 SDUs, but the sector’s Information Density only allows 30 SDUs, you’ll only receive 30 if successful</p><h3 id="h_01KBJ76J011JR2AMX6NTDYZ9M7">Start Scanning</h3><p>There are two ways to initiate a scan:</p><h4 id="h_01KBJ74GW0S3TBFNA56VRETX4P">Method A – Classic Scan:</h4><ul><li><p>Select your <strong>undocked fleet</strong></p></li><li><p>Click <strong>"Scan"</strong> in the bottom control panel</p></li><li><p>Sign the transaction in your wallet (first time scanning in a sector may require an extra registration transaction)</p></li></ul><p><img class="wysiwyg-image-resized hs-image-align-none" style="aspect-ratio: 321/383; height: auto; width: 321px;" src="https://20489070.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/20489070/image-png-Jun-19-2025-05-28-06-1158-PM.png" width="321" height="383"></p><h4 id="h_01KBJ74GW0XP5XQDX3C6TZ2SQG">Method B – Sector Survey Panel:</h4><ul><li><p>Toggle <strong>“Sector Survey”</strong> in the top-right of the screen</p><p><img class="wysiwyg-image-resized hs-image-align-none" style="aspect-ratio: 260/317; height: auto; width: 260px;" src="https://20489070.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/20489070/image-png-Jun-19-2025-05-28-40-0980-PM.png" width="260" height="317"></p></li><li><p>Click <strong>“Scan”</strong> next to any idle fleet<img class="hs-image-align-none" style="height: auto;" src="https://20489070.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/20489070/image-png-Jun-19-2025-05-29-34-5483-PM.png" width="688" height="105"></p></li><li><p>See a real-time <strong>cooldown countdown</strong> after scanning</p><p><img class="wysiwyg-image-resized hs-image-align-none" style="aspect-ratio: 260/216; height: auto; width: 260px;" src="https://20489070.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/20489070/image-png-Jun-19-2025-05-30-24-2134-PM.png" width="260" height="216"></p></li></ul><p>Use <strong>“Scan All”</strong> to trigger multiple fleet scans at once—just remember, each one requires a transaction signature.</p><h3 id="h_01KBJ76J01PZD0GX8NKYGMGR9R">Review Scan Results</h3><p>A popup will notify you of the scan outcome:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> You’ll receive SDUs directly in your fleet’s cargo</p></li><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> You’ll see your chance % and suggested retry timing</p></li></ul><p>Even a failed scan tells you useful info about a sector’s Information Density.</p><h3 id="h_01KBJ76J010R2FK4E07A89W247">Best Ships for Scanning</h3><p>These <strong>Data Runners</strong> are optimized for scanning:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Opal Rayfam</strong> (Small)</p></li><li><p><strong>VZUS opod</strong> (Medium)</p></li><li><p><strong>Fimbul BYOS Ranger</strong> (Medium)</p></li></ul><p>They use no food and have high SDU/Scan stats.</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

